 omitted because the complete names of the Performance Evaluation Center, Interstate Commerce Commission, Railroad Safety System Program, Technical Assistance Panel, and Secretary of Transportation are used the first time the terms appear in a section. The words “characterized by transportation” are omitted as surplus.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In clause (3), the text of 45:502(5)(A) and the words “on and after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1979-10-01"},"text":"October 1, 1979","children":[],"tail":"” are omitted as obsolete. Reference to 45:564(e) is omitted as obsolete because 45:564(e) was repealed by section 1183(d) of the Omnibus Budget Reconciliation Act of 1981 ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/35"},"text":"Public Law 97–35","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/95/697"},"text":"95 Stat. 697","children":[],"tail":")."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In clauses (4) and (10), the words “authority, corporation, or other” are omitted as surplus.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In clause (4), the words “and includes the Metropolitan Transportation Authority, the Connecticut Department of Transportation, the Maryland Department of Transportation the Southeastern Pennsylvania Transportation Authority, the New Jersey Transit Corporation, the Massachusetts Bay Transportation Authority, the Port Authority Trans-Hudson Corporation, any successor agencies, and any entity created by one or more such agencies for the purpose of operating” are omitted as surplus.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In clause (5), the words “whether within or across the geographical boundaries of a State” are omitted as surplus.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Clause (9) is added to eliminate repetition of the words “fares or charges” throughout this part.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idcb2c0e77-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idcb2c0e78-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The date of enactment of the Passenger Rail Investment and Improvement Act of 2008, referred to in par. (7)(C), is the date of enactment of div. B of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/432"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–432","children":[],"tail":", which was approved "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2008-10-16"},"text":"Oct. 16, 2008","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idcb2c0e79-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2019—Par. (7)(D)(ii). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/420"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–420","children":[],"tail":" substituted “chapter 229” for “chapter 244”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2015—Pars. (5) to (13). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/94"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–94","children":[],"tail":" added pars. (5), (6), (12), and (13) and redesignated former pars. (5) to (9) as (7) to (11), respectively."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2008—Pars. (2) to (5). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/432"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–432","children":[],"tail":" added par. (5), redesignated former pars. (3) to (5) as (2) to (4), respectively, and struck out former par. (2) which read as follows: “ ‘basic system’ means the system of intercity rail passenger transportation designated by the Secretary of Transportation under section 4 of the Amtrak Improvement Act of 1978 and approved by Congress, and transportation required to be provided under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t49/s24705/a"},"text":"section 24705(a) of this title","children":[],"tail":" and section 4(g) of the Act, including changes in the system or transportation that Amtrak makes using the route and service criteria.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1997—Pars. (2) to (6). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/134/s407/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–134, § 407(1)","children":[],"tail":", (2), redesignated pars. (3) to (7) as (2) to (6), respectively, and struck out former par. (2) which read as follows: “ ‘avoidable loss’ means the avoidable costs of providing rail passenger transportation, less revenue attributable to the transportation, as determined by the Interstate Commerce Commission under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s553"},"text":"section 553 of title 5","children":[],"tail":".”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (7). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/134/s407/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–134, § 407(2)","children":[],"tail":", (3), redesignated par. (8) as (7) and inserted “, including a unit of State or local government,” after “means a person”. Former par. (7) redesignated (6)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Pars. (8) to (10). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/134/s407/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–134, § 407(2)","children":[],"tail":", redesignated pars. (8) to (10) as (7) to (9), respectively."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (11). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/134/s407/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–134, § 407(1)","children":[],"tail":", struck out par. (11) which read as follows: “ ‘route and service criteria’ means the criteria and procedures for making route and service decisions established under section 404(c)(1)–(3)(A) of the Rail Passenger Service Act.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idcb2c0e7a-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idcb2c0e7b-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2015 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/94"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–94","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2015-10-01"},"text":"Oct. 1, 2015","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/94/s1003"},"text":"section 1003 of Pub. L. 114–94","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s5313"},"text":"section 5313 of Title 5","children":[],"tail":", Government Organization and Employees."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
